r4847 | mcgrathr@chromium.org | Tue Apr 12 13:37:00 PDT 2011

Changed paths:
 M http://src.chromium.org/viewvc/chrome/trunk/src/native_client/tools/Makefile.gcc?r1=4847&amp;r2=4846&amp;pathrev=4847

Use -mtls-use-call in libstdc++ build.

This adds -mtls-use-call to the compilation flags used for libraries
in the GCC build, particularly libstdc++ is of interest.  This is needed
for for the integrated runtime blob, which will link in libstdc++ and
must segregate IRT-private TLS uses from user TLS.

